# coq
#
# Coq is a formal proof management system. It provides a formal language to
# write mathematical definitions, executable algorithms and theorems together
# with an environment for semi-interactive development of machine-checked
# proofs. Typical applications include the certification of properties of
# programming languages (e.g. the CompCert compiler certification project, or
# the Bedrock verified low-level programming library), the formalization of
# mathematics (e.g. the full formalization of the Feit-Thompson theorem or
# homotopy type theory) and teaching.
#
# https://coq.inria.fr/
brew install coq

# cowsay
#
# cowsay / cowthink - configurable speaking/thinking cow (and a bit more)
#
# Cowsay generates an ASCII picture of a cow saying  something  provided  by
